  "body": "# Feature Issue\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to Share an image **so that** I can send images to apps and contacts outside of Status. \r\nAs a user I want to Save an image **so that** I can keep it for later use.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like and include designs and Figma links if available.)\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the use cases the implementation should cover. E.g. New users, existing users, public chat, group chat, etc)\r\n*Summary*: As per feature request #11912 \r\n\r\nShare image comes with a [design update](https://www.figma.com/file/aS1ct66VQ6V0cio7vSqS8UoG/Chat?node-id=4190%3A24449) that should apply to Android and iOS. Currently the implementation differs between Android and iOS (see #12474) \r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\n- Share option is available when viewing image in full screen\r\n- UI is update to reflect design update\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Rules for the future PR to be accepted.)\r\n\r\n### Notes\r\n\r\n- Note that this request is somewhat orthogonal to e.g. blocking screenshots and might need community debate to understand if easily sharing images outside of Status is desirable from a privacy point of view. That said, the ability to share is already available albeit with a workaround by either saving and sharing the image or enabling screenshots and sharing an image \r\n- Note that this issue is distinct from #12148, which describes ability to Share an image to Status\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (For the developer who will implement. Include planning poker estimates, guidance, etc.)\r\n",
